sentences: Nikki Anne Iles  (née Burnham; born 16 May 1963) is a British jazz composer, pianist and educator.
Iles was born in Dunstable, Bedfordshire, on 16 May 1963.

She started her musical education at primary school, where she learnt to play the harmonica and the clarinet, and at eleven years old she won a junior exhibition at the Royal Academy of Music, where she studied clarinet and piano from 1974 to 1981.

She went on to the Leeds College of Music (1981–1984).
Iles won the 1996 John Dankworth Special Award at the BT Jazz Festival.
Iles was awarded the British Empire Medal (BEM) in the 2022 New Year Honours for services to music.
